525749819.text: "Accordingly, mTOR activity is exquisitely sensitive to cell energy status, sensed through a complex circuitry involving the AMP activated kinase, a serine threonine kinase activated by the reduction of intracellular ATP and the increase of AMP and ATP ratio [XREF_BIBR] Phosphorylation of the TSC1 and TSC2 complex by AMPK and the consequent inactivation of the GTPase Rheb, an upstream activator of mTOR, profoundly inhibits mTOR signaling, thereby reducing protein synthesis and promoting cell survival under nutrient restriction [XREF_BIBR]."
